Package: AutoXplainR
Title: Stress-Testing Evidence Behind Model Explanations
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person(
      given = "Matteo",
      family = "Mazzarelli",
      email = "matteo.mazzarelli@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
Description: Audits the reliability of model-agnostic explanations for tabular
    predictive models. Repeated permutation importance is paired with Monte
    Carlo stability, feature-dependence diagnostics, comparison across supplied
    near-optimal models, accumulated local effects, and provenance-rich HTML
    evidence reports. Optional adapters support 'H2O' AutoML, interactive
    'Plotly' graphics, and evidence-constrained remote narratives.
